@node A Camera Example
@section A Camera Example

The @code{Camera} example introduces the system component
(@xref{Systems}).  The system diagram (@xref{Invoking dzn graph}) looks
like this:

@image{images/Camera-system,6in,,,.png}

This is what the Camera system looks like in Dezyne:
@example
component Camera
@{
  provides IControl control;

  system
  @{
    Driver driver;
    Acquisition acquisition;
    Optics optics;

    control <=> driver.control;
    driver.acquisition <=> acquisition.port;
    driver.optics <=> optics.port;
  @}
@}
@end example

It introduces the following concepts:
@table @code
@item provides IControl control;
Similar to a regular component, it defines ports,
@item system
The @code{system} specification defines @emph{instances} of components
and their @emph{bindings},
@item Driver driver;
A component instance named @code{driver} of type @code{Driver},
@item Acquisition acquisition;
A component instance named @code{acquisition} of type @code{Acquisition},
which is a @code{system} component itself,
@item Optics optics;
An instance of another @code{system} component,
@item control <=> driver.control;
A binding of the @code{Camera}'s port @code{control} to the port named
@code{control} of the @code{driver} instance.
@item driver.acquisition <=> acquisition.port;
A binding between pairs of ports on component instances.
@end table

The light blue components in the system view, such as @code{lens} are
@emph{foreign} components (@xref{Components}); their definition
looks like this:

@example
component Lens
@{
  provides ILens port;
@}
@end example

A foreign component does not specify any implementation: neither a
@code{behavior} nor a @code{system}; its behavior is said to be
implementation elsewhere, and in a foreign language (in this case
@code{C++}).

The full example is contained in the source tree at
@file{test/all/Camera/Camera.dzn} or
@url{https://savannah.nongnu.org/cgit/dezyne.git/dezyne/tree/test/all/Camera/Camera.dzn,
Camera.dzn}.

