@node Well-formedness -- Valued Actions and Calls
@section Well-formedness -- Valued Actions and Calls

Both @code{action}s and function @code{call}s can be valued, and as such
are considered to be expressions.  They can only be called are from the
imperative statement.  The reason is that @code{action}s and function
@code{calls} (at least the functions that contain @code{action}s) cause
a side effect.

This means that @code{action}s or function @code{call}s cannot be used
to initialize the value of a global variable in a behavior, neither
can it be used in a @code{guard} statement.

@menu
* Action in member variable initializer::
* Call in member variable initializer::
* Action value discarded::
* Call value discarded::
@end menu

